                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.00/97: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-24T12:00:00+03:06"
                            >July 24, 1943—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>71. Personal for Alling. Department’s 911 to Cairo, July 10, 10 p.m.<note n="85"
                        xml:id="d836fn85">Not printed.</note> Hoskins now in Cairo has just advised
                    me of purpose of his mission but gave few details. Although I will do everything
                    possible to assist him, I am not hopeful of any beneficial result. The King will
                    not be happy to have to choose between prejudicing his position in the Moslem
                    world or refusing the proposals of his friends. He will not compromise his
                    principles as he conceives them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
